---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import teamVisual from '../assets/images/perfume-about-us-info.png';
import '../styles/about-team.css';
---

<section class="about-team">
  <div class="container about-team__container">
    <p class="about-team__label">Team</p>
    <h2 class="about-team__title">The Noses Behind Mimya</h2>
    <p class="about-team__intro">
      Mimya is powered by a team of fragrance journalists, chemists, and lifelong collectors. We have spent decades smelling, tasting, and studying
      the olfactory arts. We are the people who stop you next to what your new wear gave - not to sell you something, but to appreciate the art on your skin.
    </p>

    <div class="about-team__visual">
      <Image
        src={teamVisual}
        alt="Team fragrance visual"
        class="about-team__image"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
        widths={[480, 768, 1024, 1400]}
        sizes="(max-width: 992px) 100vw, 860px"
      />
      <button type="button" class="about-team__play" aria-label="Preview visual">▶</button>
    </div>

    <div class="about-team__details">
      <p>
        <strong>Fragrance is Subjective, But Quality is Objective.</strong> We acknowledge that scent is deeply personal. However, we evaluate perfumes based on the quality
        of ingredients, the originality of the composition, and the technical skill of the blend. We look for artistry over marketing budgets.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Education First.</strong> The best consumer is an educated one. We strive to provide the vocabulary you need to articulate your preferences, turning a vague
        "I like this" into "I love the contrast between the smoky vetiver and the bright bergamot."
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-team__actions">
      <a href="/blog" class="btn btn-primary">Explore Our Blog</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>